Cell.Text: [S] G|How did you get it? No, never mind, I probably shouldn't know. | I see... it looks like Suvaris has been traveling to Dawnstar to meet with a pirate crew there. | Get to Dawnstar and see what you can find out about these rogues. I'd wager they won't be too far from the tavern. | Try to find out where their fortress is. The captain, Stig Salt-Plank, has to know something.
[S] G|Just in time. This is Adelaisa, one of my superiors from the Company. | She's been dispatched to... eh... see to it that we get back on schedule. | You should probably speak to her.

Node.Caption: MS10OrthusKnowIslandBranchTopic: I know where the Blood Horkers are.

Cell.Text: [S] G|I can't express how much easier you've made my job. | Maybe Adelaisa will finally ease up, but I expect she won't. | Ah, yes, your pay. The Company thanks you for your services. Should we ever be able to help you, stop by.

Node.Caption: MS10OrthusRewardBranchTopic: The pirate haven has been destroyed.

Cell.Text: We used to think the pirates had an army of battlemages at their side. | As it turns out, it was just one. Haldyn. I've since learned more about him. | The most dangerous sort of man -- quick to anger, but patient in exacting vengeance. | He also has a fearsome control of Destruction magic. | I wish you the best of luck.

Node.Caption: MS10OrthusHaldynBranchTopic: What do you know about Haldyn?

Cell.Text: Finally, someone around here that can get things done. | Since we're short on soldiers you'll be coming with us, too. No arguments. | Anything else you want to say?

Node.Caption: MS10AdelaisaKnowIslandBranchTopic: I know where the Blood Horkers are.

Cell.Text: [S] G|Haldyn? I've heard of the man, but never guess he'd join up with some pirates. | This could be even more dangerous than I thought. Head to the ships. We'll plan the assault on the way.

Node.Caption: MS10AdelaisaWarnAboutHaldyn: Their leader is a battle-mage named Haldyn.

Cell.Text: [S] Well, here we are. We think.

[S] G|You've shown yourself useful so far. All these lunks are too afraid of Haldyn to head in before the fog's cleared. | So if you're willing to perform one more service for the Company, we could put this matter behind us for good. | Take out Haldyn, and we'll handle the rest.
Hard to say. The weather's taken a bit of a turn, here. | Haldyn's been known to obscure his hideaways with magic. | If we take care of him, the way should be clear to properly assault the island.

[S] Impressive work. We started the attack once you made the fog scamper away like that. | Hope you didn't catch any of the fire. | We can head back whenever you're set. There's celebrating to be done!
G|Let me know. We should stay here all day. My men want their mead.
